      "comment": "NIGHT FLIGHT (7) is in good form having placed in two of his last three starts. Came from the back row and finished third at his latest appearance at Ballarat, beaten 4.4 metres. Must overcome a very wide draw but with even luck he is good enough to take out a race like this. CHARLIE WALKER (9) had been racing consistently before scoring last week at Ballarat, getting home by 5 metres after leading. The back row draw presents a challenge but if things go his was he could make it consecutive wins. LOVE WHO (6) worked and faded last start but placed at Terang prior. At peak fitness now and won the only time he attempted this circuit and distance. ALLWATFUNJINGLES (5) is in the mix following a solid fifth at his most recent appearance at Ballarat.",
